# FOGUS Cursor Rules

This file is intentionally short. Use `.github/copilot-instructions.md` as the primary shared guidance.
For workflow-sensitive work, read `AI_WORKFLOW_GUARD.md` and treat `docs/workflow-policy.json` as canonical.

## Always Follow

- Use Supabase `sb_publishable_` and `sb_secret_` keys only.
- In Next.js 16 dynamic routes, use async params and `await props.params`.
- Keep LINE LIFF registered at `/liff` and preserve LIFF safe-area padding.
- Do not expose `SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY` to browser code.
- Reuse workflow states, unit conversion, and pricing rules from `src/lib/types.ts`.

## Source Of Truth

- Workflow and domain constants: `src/lib/types.ts`
- Auth and public route boundaries: `src/lib/middleware.ts`
- Schema evolution: `supabase/migrations/`
- Environment setup: `docs/ENV_AND_LINE_SETUP.md`

## Validation

- `npm run dev`
- `npm run build`
- `npm run lint`
